The paper deals with the problem of pricing in multi-unit markets with budgets, which is a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing optimal pricing schemes, which falls under the category of optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.AI). The paper further discusses the concept of strategyproofness in pricing mechanisms, which is a central topic in mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper provides hardness results and approximation algorithms, which are common in theoretical computer science and machine learning (cs.LG).
